# Knotwork — the bass: fat but TIGHT. unison 2 with only 7 cents
# spread — two cards for width and beat, not a detuned mess (bass must
# stay pitch-solid). Square + saw slightly apart over a phase-locked
# sub square = the two-oscillator Moog bottom with weight underneath.
# Ladder at 700, resonance LOW (0.5, no quack), a firm +0.8 oct filter
# kick over 180 ms for the consonant, then a SUSTAINED tone. Drive 2.6:
# the ladder's own saturation is the grain. Fast release so 16th motor
# figures articulate cleanly.
unison 2
unison_detune 7
waveform 1
pulse_width 0.45
osc2_wave 2
osc2_pitch 0
osc2_level 0.5
osc3_wave 0
osc3_pitch 0
osc3_level 0
detune 3
sub 0.4
circuit 0
key_track 0.4
osc_fm 0
sync 0
ring 0
glide 0
attack 0.005
decay 0.4
sustain 0.7
release 0.12
filter_env 0.8
filter_attack 0.003
filter_decay 0.18
filter_sustain 0.45
filter_release 0.15
cutoff 700
resonance 0.5
drive 2.6
saturation 1.05
hpf 25
volume 0.5
octave 4
noise 0
fuzz 0
spring 0
lfo_rate 0.5
lfo_shape 0.5
lfo_pitch 0
lfo_filter 0
lfo_pwm 0
